Lessons and Retrospectives from past runs of this project (Do NOT repeat these mistakes):
Past Run #1:
- What went well: - The CSS-based cell-centered intersection grid alignment strategy worked beautifully to shift pieces from cell centers to line intersections.
- No JavaScript coordinates or matrix index mapping logic had to be modified, avoiding any potential logic bugs or AI pathfinding errors.
- Custom class mapping for palace diagonal quadrants and center cells allowed drawing perfect 'X' lines using absolute-positioned pseudo-elements.
- All unit tests across all games in the hub pass 100% with no regressions.
- What went wrong: - Escaping JSON arguments in Powershell for python scripts run directly can strip quotes and cause JSON parsing failures on the command line. Solved by writing helper scripts to read config files and parameter variables dynamically.
- Prompt suggestions: - Use CSS variables, size/position overrides, and :nth-child grid selectors to easily render line intersections on standard grid layouts without restructuring underlying HTML cells.
- Lessons learned: - Gradients positioned at cell centers with customized :nth-child boundaries are highly effective for drawing clean chess board grids on native CSS grid structures.

Past Run #2:
- What went well: The CSS intersection-based board rendering strategy for Chinese Chess worked flawlessly. By centering custom variable gradients on cell containers and using coordinate-based selectors for diagonals and edge lines, the board layout is clean, responsive, and keeps pieces perfectly aligned without modifying Javascript matrix index mappings. Unit tests pass 100%.
- What went wrong: None in this run, as the changes were already fully integrated and verified via self-subagents. Some minor PowerShell quotes escaping issues occurred but were bypassed by utilizing temporary arguments files.
- Prompt suggestions: When generating task parameters via command-line shell utilities on Windows environments, prefer saving to a file and passing the file path to prevent PowerShell quotes stripping.
- Lessons learned: Coordinate-based custom selectors and gradients offer a highly powerful way to override grid lines on grid containers without introducing additional elements. Keep a checklist of environment capabilities (such as python scripts or existing files in scratch folder) to easily call real MCP backend connections.

